main event: An unusual bright object was observed traveling from east to west at high speed on September 23, 1963.
interesting points: The object was described as triangular in shape and brilliantly lit.,Witnesses were able to observe the object through binoculars at 10x magnification.,The sighting lasted for a duration of approximately 5 minutes.,The report was associated with a radio station prior to the sighting.,The individual who reported is an ex-pilot with Air Force experience.
witness description: an ex-pilot, his wife, and a friend
